# INStartCallCallRecordToCallBackResolutionResult

**Class**

A resolution result for the redial capabilities of a missed call.

## Declaration

```swift
class INStartCallCallRecordToCallBackResolutionResult
```

## Overview

You return an `INStartCallCallRecordToCallBackResolutionResult` object when resolving parameters containing an [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INCallRecord] value. Use the creation method that best reflects your ability to resolve the parameter successfully. The resolved value can be different from the original [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INCallRecord]. This flexibility allows app extensions to apply business logic constraints.

Use [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INIntentResolutionResult/notRequired()] to continue with a `nil` value. For additional resolution operators, see [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INIntentResolutionResult].

## Initializers

- **init(callRecordResolutionResult:)**: Creates an object whose resolution involves successfully redialing a call.

## Type Methods

- **unsupported(forReason:)**: Creates a result that requires the user to confirm the request, because your app is unable to support the current request.

## Resolution Results

- **INCallRecordResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the details of a call.
- **INCallRecordTypeResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the types of calls that your app handled.
- **INCallDestinationTypeResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the destination type of a call.
- **INCallCapabilityResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the call capability for the call.
- **INCallRecordTypeOptionsResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the call types to include in a search.
- **INStartCallContactResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the contact for the call.
- **INStartCallCallCapabilityResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the call capability for the call.

## Inherits From

- INCallRecordResolutionResult

## Conforms To

- CVarArg
- CustomDebugStringConvertible
- CustomStringConvertible
- Equatable
- Hashable
- NSObjectProtocol
